# PreLabeler DRY/SOLID Rule

Quy tắc **heuristic labeling** (macro fallback, NHB/NUM/ALY/STR/POI đặc thù) được mô tả chi tiết trong `.cursor/rules/prelabeler-labeling-heuristics.mdc` — cập nhật song song khi đổi `PreLabeler.predict` hoặc bộ case.

## Version

- **Current:** `v2.3.0`
- **Updated:** `2026-05-09`
- **Scope:** Predictor/service/UI strict behavior + random-predict consistency

## Single Source of Truth

| Concern | Canonical file | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Rule-based predictor (`PreLabeler.predict`, `export_data`) | `app/ai/export_for_annotation.py` | Algorithm layer only. |
| Build expected, admin Type+Name, two-way validation | `app/services/prelabeler_labeling_service.py` | Domain layer only. |
| Admin prefix vocabulary (`WDS`, `DST`, `PRO`) + union (`ADMIN_ALL_PREFIXES_ALT`) | `app/ai/constants.py` | Used by both predictor and service via `admin_prefix_anchored_pattern`, `admin_presence_pattern`, `ADMIN_PREFIX_ALTERNATIVES`, `ADMIN_PRESENCE_ALTERNATIVES`, `ADMIN_ALL_PREFIXES_ALT`. |
| Labeling test cases (data) | `scripts/labeling/prelabeler_labeling_cases.json` | Single canonical dataset. |

## Rules

- Do NOT duplicate labeling-case domain logic across endpoints or scripts.
- Do NOT redeclare `Phường|Xã|...|Thành phố|Tỉnh|...` regex literals anywhere; always derive from `app/ai/constants.py`.
- `random-predict`, `run`, refresh and regression scripts must call shared functions in `app/services/prelabeler_labeling_service.py` (`predictions_to_expected`, `enforce_admin_type_name`, `validate_expected_against_actual`, `first_expected_text`).
- Any change to expected-building or validation rules must be implemented in the shared service first, then consumed by callers.
- Any change to admin prefix vocabulary must be implemented in `app/ai/constants.py` first, then consumed via the helpers — never via copy/paste.
- Preserve `Type + Name` for all labels, especially admin units (`WDS`, `DST`, `PRO`) when present in raw text.
- `strict=true`: two-way validation strict (missing expected OR unexpected actual => fail).
- `strict=false`: only enforce missing-expected/admin-validation; unexpected is informational.
- UI default strict must be `true` for newly created/random cases unless user explicitly turns it off.
- `random-predict` and `run` must stay consistent for admin normalization (`Type + Name`) and same-name DST/PRO disambiguation.

## Required Checks After Changes

- Run `python -m py_compile` for edited Python files.
- Run `python scripts/labeling/run_prelabeler_labeling_cases.py` — must report 100% pass for the current suite size (see JSON array length).
- Run `python scripts/test/test_prelabeler_regression.py` — must print `OK`.
- If API behavior changes, verify `/api/prelabeler-cases/random-predict` and `/api/prelabeler-cases/run` are consistent.

